{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d8bde45e-0a41-4cec-9ca9-d3c6ed6f70a7","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nFor xUnit `[Theory]` tests, use `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` instead.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d979b3ae-47fb-4952-9d75-afd8b96619a7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to skip tests with a reason message in four different .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":319,"requestId":"BC28:26D998:1CD677C:1FF8AD1:69FA9397"},"id":"3cff3e34-652d-4617-bcd5-05df3ae60d6e","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:04:32.018Z","parentId":"8f80d1c6-3b34-4ed6-acd3-d45f333ada36"}
